inn1.comm: Lee's on target straightaway, slightly short of length, just outside off, Akmal blocks it off the front foot
Lee grunts as he sends down that delivery, again it's close to offstump, Akmal content to defend
first run for Pakistan, a streaky one at that, glides off Akmal's outside edge wide of slips to third man
back of a length, in the corridor outside off, Afridi feels for it and is beaten, good delivery that
again the ball shapes away a touch after pitching just outside off, Afridi flirts with it and is beaten again
speared into the pads this time, was sliding down the leg, that ends a testing first over from Lee
Siddle starts with a shortish ball on off, Akmal rocks back and guides it down to third man
a lot more confident from Afridi, gets well forward and taps the ball towards the off side
Afridi gets going with a boundary, a half-volley outside off, Afridi lashes it down the ground past a diving mid-off
Siddle shortens his length, on middle and off this time, Afridi shuffles across and pats the ball to the leg side
full on middle and leg, Akmal bunts it towards midwicket for a single
Afridi ends the over with a superb flick through midwicket, Siddle erred by overpitching on the pads
Lee pegs away at offstump, Akmal blocks towards point
keeps a touch lower than Akmal expected, he's struck on the pads but the ball is slanting down the leg side
shortish and wide, Akmal chases after it but misses, not much footwork from Akmal in that stroke
a 145.6kmh bouncer from Lee, just outside off, Akmal sways out of the way
Lee remains accurate, just around off, pushing Akmal onto the backfoot, the batsman defends to the off side
length ball just outside off, Akmal jabs it towards third man for a run
Akmal shows the full face of the bat as he punches the ball straight towards mid-off
full and wide, scythed down to third man for a single
slightly slower from Siddle, guided behind a diving backward point, a lot of confused calling from the batsmen as they wait to see whether it beats the fielder before they decide on taking the run
batsman gets forward and defends the ball towards cover
extra cover does the fielding this time, that was a length ball on middle and off
the batsmen zip through for a single after the ball is played with soft hands between cover and extra cover
length ball on the pads, Akmal stays in the crease and defends
full ball on off, punched back to the bowler who fields and gets in position to fling it at the stumps, Lee doesn't throw the ball but Akmal scampers away from the stump just to be safe
Lee keeping it full, on middle and leg this time, blocked towards midwicket
back of a length just outside off, pushed off the front foot towards cover
Afridi decides to try something different to shake Lee off his tight line and length, skips away from legstump, Lee keeps it on a length outside off, Afridi swings at it but misses

Afridi's nearly run-out there, he punches the ball to Johnson at mid-off and starts sprinting for the single, Akmal sends him back, Johnson misses the stumps at the keeper's end, a direct hit and Afridi was gone
short and wide, thank you very much says Akmal, and smashes that over point for four
far better ball from Siddle, length ball closer to off, Akmal edges it towards slips, bottom hand came off as he played that, the ball doesn't carry
a yorker on middle, dug out back towards the bowler
short ball on off stump, Akmal decides t play it on the front foot, jabs it uppishly towards cover, lands a few yards short of the fielder
length ball on middle and leg, nicely driven by Akmal towards mid-on but doesn't beat the fielder
this time the fielders have no chance, Akmal gets a big stride in and caresses the ball past extra cover for four
short of length, again heading for offstump, Afridi taps it towards cover
the Mad Max in Afridi makes an appearance, a length ball outside off, Afridi throws a wild heave at it, misses the ball
this time Afridi is beaten as he goes for the drive, Lee keeps nagging just outside off
nice shot from Afridi, overpitched on middle and leg, Afridi shuffles across and whips it past midwicket for a beautifully-timed boundary
Lee responds by reverting to his length ball outside off formula, Afridi is beaten as he looks to defend that one
length ball, heading for the top of off, Afridi skips across and tucks the ball down to fine leg for a single

he strikes first ball, Afridi's gone, shortish ball on legstump, Afridi is hurried into playing a pull, the ball lobs towards square leg, Hopes makes plenty of ground to his right from midwicket and latches onto the ball
Johnson bangs it in again, angling across Akmal who defends towards the covers
fuller this time, going across the batsman, who is content to shoulder arms
length ball on the pads, clipped towards square leg
Johnson appeals for a caught-behind, there was a noise as the ball passed the bat but it was from bat hitting pad, well spotted by the umpire
Younis stands tall and defends the ball towards cover, end of a successful over from Johnson
Shot! for the second time today Akmal carves the ball uppishly over point for four
superb reply from Lee, 142.9kmh, a length ball moving just a hint away from the batsman, who plays inside the line of the ball as it goes through to the keeper
back of a length, heading for middle, Akmal looks to turn that to the leg side but mistimes it towards the bowler
length ball, on middle and leg, Akmal gets forward and punches it towards mid-on

short and wide from Lee, Akmal slahes it towards Johnson at third man, that flew flat and fast towards the fielder who decides to wait and take it on the bounce, Lee looks at the fielder as though he expected him to dive forward for a catch
well outside off, Younis shoulders arms
Australia don't seem to learn that's it's bad idea to give Akmal room outside off, Akmal cuts that powerfully in front of point for four
on the legstump, Akmal swivels and guides the ball towards fine leg
full and wide from Johnson, Younis reaches across for it but doesn't make contact
short of length ball, Younis pokes it towards backward point, and immediately yells 'No, no, no' to the non-striker who wondered whether there was a single
same length, on legstump this time, brushed off the thigh pad towards the leg side
wonderful shot from Younis to end the over, leans across and gracefully drives the ball through covers for four
slower ball, stays a touch low and Akmal is nearly beaten
Akmal cuts to point
on off and Akmal drives to cover confidently
outside off, Younis leaves it alone
swings in to pitch on off, quite a full delivery and Younis defends
outside off and short, Younis leans back and cuts past point fielder for four
length ball just outside off, Akmal carves that over point, James Hopes dives at the boundary to cut it off
defended of the backfoot towards the off side
shortish ball, angling across, guided down to third man for a single
on the leg stump, tucked towards square leg, Hauritz is onto the ball quickly
again third man has work to do as Younis dabs the ball with the angle
length ball outside off, Akmal gets forward and crunches that over extra cover for a boundary, he's getting into the groove here
full ball, punched back towards the bowler
length ball on offstump, Younis opens the face to get the ball towards backward point, easy single
slightly overpitched outside off, Akmal gets a big stride in as he looks to bash the ball past extra cover, mistimes it to the off side
slanting into offstump, defended watchfully towards the off side
full and outside off, crunched towards Ponting at cover
Akmal stretches forward and opens the face to guide the ball towards point
Akmal pokes the ball towards cover point
sweetly timed from Akmal, who is looking dangerous here, gets forward and crashes it past short cover
short and wide, Akmal rocks wide and cuts it towards backward point, doesn't beat the fielder
overpitched and well outside off, Akmal shoulders arms to that one
a yorker just outside off, bunted to third man for a single
back of a length,on off, played with soft hands towards cover point
Akmal's cover driving has been fantastic today, gives us another demonstration, this time sweeper cover is around to cut it off
Younis rocks back and slashes that hard towards third man, the batsmen zip through for two
back of a length ball outside off, Younis is content to leave that for the keeper
very full, just outside off, Younis looks to crunch it past mid-off, but mistimes it there
slightly short of length, Younis Khan goes for the cut, gets a bottom edge which misses the stumps and reaches the keeper on the bounce
Younis dabs this towards backward point for a single
dropped, tough chance, a full ball is punched back to Johnson, about chest high, but Johnson can't pull off the catch as he's half-way through his follow-through
bangs in the bouncer, Younis ducks under
short ball angling across the batsman, wide enough to be left alone
Johnson, as he does once in a while, loses his radar, a wild delivery way outside off, would have been a wide even in a Test
length ball on the pads, tucked towards square leg, straight towards the fielder
slightly fuller, same line, Younis works it square leg again, a scoring chance missed there
Younis is surprised by the extra lift, the ball rises sharply  after pitching on a length, on middle stump, he is struck on the chest

another chance, Akmal waltzes down the track and bludgeons the ball toward sweeper cover, where Hauritz doesn't pick it up, moves forward and dives only at the last moment, gets a hand on it but can't hang on to it
Akmal shows the full face of the bat as he pushes the ball to mid-on
a bouncer aimed at Akmal's body, he does well to get under the ball
Akmal is beaten outside off, a length ball which Akmal wafts at
short of length, slanting into off, Akmal goes back and defends solidly
that ball stays down, Akmal tries to adjust late as he looks to defend to the off, he's beaten, the ball reaches the keeper after the second bounce
jabbed towards cover for a quick single
get behind the line of that offstump ball and defends towards the bowler
shortish ball, Akmal shovels it towards deep midwicket for a single
back of length, just outside off, dabbed towards backward point
Younis shuffles across and clips the ball off his thigh pad towards midwicket
that ends a tidy Hopes over, the batsman tips the ball just in front of point
Watson grunts as  he sends down a quick bouncer, 141kmh, too high for the umpire's liking
this one keeps low, Akmal was on the backfoot, adjusts late, gets bat on it, nicks it on the bounce to the keeper
length ball just outside off, Akmal opens the face to steer the ball towards backward point
Watson gets rid of Akmal, who goes for a flamboyant pull but only manages to bottom-edge the ball onto the base of legstump
Malik gets confidently forward and defends the ball towards extra cover
another ball that stayed low, Malik bends after walking across the stumps to clip the ball behind square leg
a typical Younis Khan 'No,no,no,no,no' after he pushes the ball towards cover
Malik pushes at the ball well ahead of his body, gets a bit of an outside edge towards deep backward point
steady from Hopes, aiming for offstump, blocked back to the bowler
almost another played-on there, Younis tries a cute dab but gets a bottom edge which is perilously close to the stumps, bounces over, luckily for him
gets a big stride in and punches the ball towards extra cover
Hopes continues to keep the runs down, this ball is eased towards mid-on
poked towards cover point, Younis sets off for a single, checks whether his partner is running after taking a few steps, and then sprints down to take the run
shaping into middle and off, dropped towards cover point, Malik wants a run but is sent back
shortish ball just outside off, Younis sways under it and at the last moment pushes at it with his bat, takes the ball towards third man
defended off the front foot towards extra cover
back of length again, on middle and leg, defended back to the bowler
short ball outside off, Malik jumps to get on top of the bounce and cuts the ball to deep backward point
a full-blooded drive from Younis, placement is poor though, doesn't beat the man at short cover
Hopes keeps it around off, punched towards extra cover
a touch short from Hopes, Shoaib stands tall and defends the ball to the off side
again Malik defends stoutly, this time off the front foot
gets nicely forward and drives the ball along the ground to sweeper cover, easy single
fuller length on off, Younis Khan walks across and tucks it towards deep square leg
Shot! beautiful swing of the bat from Malik, a length ball is launched over the bowler's head and clears the boundary, hardly any power behind that stroke, all timing
full ball on middle and leg, punched along the ground towards mid-on
gets well forward and pushes an outside off ball towards mid-off this time ,again no run
keeps it on a length, just outside off, driven firmly towards short cover
fourth dot ball of the over, overpitched and wide outside off, mistimed to short cover
gets a single this time, eases the ball past the bowler towards mid-off, Siddle tries to get a hand on it but it's mid-off that has to do the fielding
Malik skips towards leg and guides the ball towards backward point
length ball outside off, left alone by the batsman, Younis is playing a measured knock here
a bit of width outside off, Younis tries to glide it towards third man but misses
Younis tips this one towards cover point, wants the single but is wisely sent back

Younis holes out to mid-on,  he was looking to loft the ball over mid-on, miscues it high in the air, Johnson races back and judges the catch well, positioning himself nicely to pouch the ball, does a rugby-style drop-kick to celebrate
guided off the backfoot towards third man for a single
back of a length ball, slanting into middle and off, defended towards cover
punched off the front foot towards mid-off, wide enough of the fielder to have time to take a single
Yousuf wafts at a back of a length delivery outside off, doesn't connect
again Yousuf is beaten outside off, this was a bit fuller from Siddle, Yousuf was looking to drive but ends up playing inside the line
a yorker on offstump, Yousuf digs it out towards extra cover
the runs are coming for Pakistan, another dot ball, this time Yousuf defends towards Hussey at cover point
slightly short, just outside off, played off the backfoot towards backward point
gets forward and defends the ball towards mid-off
slightly overpitched on the pads, whipped to square leg for a single
once more Yousuf plays and misses outside off, not much footwork as he poked at that one, misses the ball
Yousuf gets off the mark on his 8th delivery, slanting down the pads, easily runs down to fine leg for a single
length ball outside off, another easy single, Malik gets well forward and drives firmly to extra cover
shorter this time, Yousuf shuffles across and wrists the ball towards midwicket for two
tossed up, full and just outside off, driven to mid-on, where Hussey fields
a touch shorter this time, Malik plays it to Hussey's left this time to get a single
shortish ball just outside off, defended off the backfoot
lashed along the ground to long-on, 'Two, two, two' is the cry from Yousuf as he plays that shot
Malik gets forward and eases the ball towards long-on, hit too firmly to have time for two
Malik calmly picking off the singles now, he brings up Pakistan's 100 with a punch towards long-on
short ball outside off, Yousuf goes for the cut but the ball sneaks under his bat
angled into the bat, Yousuf shuffles across and tickles the ball to long leg
wide outside off, pretty full, Shoaib goes for the cut anyway, gets a bottom edge towards backward point
Yousuf stands tall and flicks wristily to midwicket, placement isn't great though
length ball outside off, Yousuf walks across his stumps, paddles the ball fine for four, Pakistan need more of these boundaries
goes for the cut but is beaten
flighted delivery, Malik gets well forward and defends
another dot ball as Malik blocks towards cover this time
fullish on middle and leg, Malik punches it back to the bowler
Malik looks to play the late cut, the ball turns a bit more than he expects, edges it towards backward point
and that's a maiden, Malik blocks towards midwicket
driven crisply off the front foot towards sweeper cover
back of a length, slanting into the pads, Yousuf turns it towards short fine leg
good shot from Malik, a slower ball from Hopes, Malik gets well forward and chips the ball over mid-off for four
sensibly eases the ball to long-on for a single
cuts in after pitching just outside off, Yousuf defends off the backfoot
length ball, homing into off, Yousuf gets forward to defend, inside-edges onto his pads
Malik continues to get the singles but driving down the ground, this time to long-off
143.3kmh, angling into the pads, turned towards square leg for a single
another single, this time dabbed down to third man
Lee fires it way down the leg side, great work from Tim Paine to stop the ball from going for five wides
Lee's back on target this time, back of a length on off, jabbed towards cover point
full and swinging in a touch, Malik gets forward and defends towards the off side
147kmh from Lee to end the over, heading for the top of off, played off the backfoot towards cover point for a single
starts with one heading towards first slip
much better this time, back of a length on the pads, tucked towards square leg
similar length but angling across the batsman, who doesn't bother with the footwork as e jabs the ball to cover point
Yousuf looks to drive outside off but is beaten
batsman gets on the backfoot and tips the ball towards backward point
soft dismissal, Malik becomes Johnson's 100th ODI victim, an innocuous delivery, full and outside off, Malik goes for the drive, he can't keep it along the ground, and finds Ponting at short cover
ooh, nearly got one more, the back of length delivery fired into offstump, gets the outside edge which flies between the keeper and a wide first slip
144.9kmh bouncer, superb delivery, just outside the line of offstump, Yousuf does well to get out of the way

what are Pakistan doing here? nearly a run-out now, Yousuf drives firmly towards Ponting at short cover, Yousuf wants the run and then decides agains it, Misbah and Yousuf are next to each other mid-pitch, Misbah turns back but would have been yards out if Ponting had got a direct hit, Misbah had hopes of making his ground because Ponting had initially misfielded
crunched to backward point off the back foot
short of length, on the pads, tucked towards midwicket
back of a length ball, heading for middle and off, defended off the backfoot
full and on the pads, whipped to deep midwicket for a single
Misbah offers a tentative prod to a back of length ball, flies off the handle towards second slip, lands short though
driven wide of mid-off, Misbah wants two but Yousuf had jogged through the first run
homing into offstump, defended watchfully towards cover point by Yousuf
shortish ball, on middle and leg, Yousuf stands on his toes and clips it towards midwicket
length ball, just outside off, defended off the backfoot by Misbah
short of length and well outside off, Misbah isn't interested in playing that one
starts the over with a bouncer outside off, left alone by Yousuf
slower ball from Lee, 107kmh, full and on the pads, clipped to midwicket
'Howzzat' say Paine as he collects the ball down the leg side, umpire isn't fooled by that and signals a wide
short of length on offstump, defended stoutly by Misbah
145.8 kmh, length ball outside off, Misbah looks to drive but the ball stays low and he is beaten
short ball, in the corridor outside off, Misbah plays with soft hands towards cover
back of a length ball on offstump, Yousuf is squared up, the ball flies off the edge towards backward point
overpitched outside off, defended back towards the bowler
back of a length just outside off, Misbah stands tall and jabs the ball towards cover point, Hussey makes a diving stop
on middle stump, length ball, Misbah whips it towards square leg for a single
length ball just outside off, defended back towards the office
full and wide, Yousuf goes for the drive but misses the ball, another dot ball
back of a length, slanting into middle, defended off the backfoot
Misbah looks to cut but is beaten by that outside off delivery
gets well forward and defends back down the pitch
well outside off, looks to defend but misses the ball
on middle and off, blocked back towards the bowler
the frustration showing for Misbah, goes for a slog sweep to a ball well outside off, again he doesn't make contact
length ball, heading for off, Misbah gets inside the line and pushes it towards cover point, takes the single to retain strike
starts off with a delivery just outside off, pushed to mid-on
a bit more width, sliced to backward point where Hussey fields
this time Misbah does get the single, gliding the ball to third man
Yousuf goes for the cut, bottom edges it almost onto his stumps
a boundary after what seems like forever, Hopes strays onto leg, Yousuf walks across and paddles it fine of long leg
chopped towards backward point to end the over
tossed up, well outside off, Yousuf eases it down to long-on for a single
an everything-behind-it heave from Misbah, mistimes towards deep midwicket, Yousuf slips, so the batsmen can't get back for the second
goes for the reverse-sweep, gets an edge which loops to his left, Paine rushesout from behind teh stumps but can't get  to the ball in time
driven with the spin towards long-on for a single
again long-on has to do the fielding, another easy single
fullish ball, Yousuf whips it towards midwicket
pushed off the front foot towards extra cover
back of length outside off, Yousuf looks to dab it to third man but he misses
angling into middle and leg this time, Yousuf gets forward and defends to the off side
back of length ball just outside off, Yousuf inside-edges it onto his pads
Misbah calls for the quick single after Yousuf backs away and taps the ball towards backward point
Misbah shuffles across and tucks the ball towards deep square leg
Pakistan's struggle for runs continues,  mistimed drive from Misbah this time to the bowler
Pakistan get to their 150 after Misbah carves the ball toward backward point for a single
driven firmly towards extra cover
big appeal for lbw as Misbah goes for the sweep, looks like he was struck just outside off, actually replays shows he's hit in line, lucky to survive
blocked back to the bowler
eased towards long-on for an easy single
full and on the pads, clipped towards square leg
shorter and just outside off, glided towards third man
finally some aggression from Pakistan's batsmen, Misbah waltzes down the pitch and clubs the ball towards wide long-on, one bounce four
steered towards wide third man for a single
Yousuf shuffles across and turns the ball from outside off towards square leg for a single
reverse-sweep from Yousuf, gets him only a single though
Misbah backs away and pushes the ball towards cover for a single
Yousuf looks to cart the ball over long-on, inside-edges onto his backfoot, the ball rolls towards the keeper
Yousuf gets across and clips the ball behind square leg for a single
clattered to long-on all along the ground
a bit of width for Yousuf, who rocks back and cuts the ball towards sweeper cover
Johnson starts with a bouncer, Yousuf defends awkwardly
Yousuf rocks onto the backfoot and dabs the ball to backward point
length ball just outside off, Yousuf drives towards mid-off
Yousuf skips away beyond leg, Johnson bowls it well outside off, Yousuf can't reach that
short ball on the leg stump, pulled to deep backward square leg for a single
shortish ball on off, defended back down the pitch
Yousuf backs away and carves the ball behind backward square leg
length ball on the leg stump, defended towards the leg side
on middle and leg, turned to midwicket for a single
Misbah skips away from leg and goes for his trademark swing over long-on, inside-edges onto his pads
comes down the pitch and looks to slog it, doesn't get hold of it and it flies to midwicket
flighted outside off, slog-swept behind deep square leg and deep midwicket for four
goes for it, pitched it up outside off, Misbah tried to dismiss it into the stands over long-off but made no contact
full outside off, chases it, ends up slicing it over the covers for a couple of runs
goes for another big one, bowled on a length outside off, swings hard and clears mid-on but not enough in it to take it to the ropes, two more
streaky but much-needed runs these, pitches it up outside off, goes for a booming drive does Misbah, gets a thick edge well wide of the diving Paine for a boundary
Johnson alters his length this time, back of a length just outside off, guided down to third man for a single
banged in short on middle, pulled away down to fine leg for a single, 10 off the over and Johnson's spell comes to an end
bowled full on the off, makes room and slices it past point into the deep for a couple of runs
shuffles, Lee sees him do so and bangs it short on the off, tries to chip it over midwicket but the shot wasn't on, just lobbed it up towards White who took a dolly at the edge of the circle
back of a length on the off, dropped into the off side short of cover for a single to give the new man the strike
off the mark, short outside off , makes room and runs it down to third man for a single
wild swing by Misbah, Lee bowled it on a good length on middle and leg, Misbah moved across a touch and tried to whack that over mid-on, was struck high on the pads
bowled short on the leg stump, helps it down to fine leg
driven well and hard, full and wide, Misbah pulls off a textbook extra-cover drive but straight to extra cover, living up to that nomenclature
another dot ball, full and wide again, MIsbah had made too much room and then decided not to go for it, couldn't reach it the big man
strikes this well, takes it on the full and slices it past point into the deep for a single
length ball on the off, drilled down to long-on for a single
moves across and drives that half-volley just wide of midwicket for a single
full and wide, driven straight to Ponting at extra cover
in the blockhole outside off, tries to ram it down the wicket, gets a thick inside edge down to deep square leg for a single
good bouncer, banged in short on middle, Umar had shaped up for the pull but it came on to him too quickly and he had to eventually back out
swing and a miss, short of a good length outside off, tries to smack it over midwicket, no contact made, bowled at 148kmph

dropped, short of a good length on the off, moves away to run it down to third man, thick edge straight to the keeper, Paine holds on for just a moment but it then pops out, sitter gone down, but also a dot ball
back of a length outside off, tries to hoick it over midwicket, a slap really, doesn't connect, another dot ball, Pakistan are struggling
another one, bowled at 151.7 kmph, identical to the previous ball, only this time Akmal wanted to smash it a little squarer, but it's too quick for the young lad, missed again
finally, juicy full toss gifted by Watson which Misbah swings for a one bounce four over midwicket
missed opportunity, low full toss outside off, drives it straight to mid-off
tries to be cheeky, bowled full outside off, sweeps it straight to midwicket, dot ball again

hit wicket, what was he doing there? Given a wide, bowled full outside off, Misbah, trying to leave it alone given the width, trotted back onto his stumps, not strange for Misbah, he's made it a habit to get out in unusual ways
Naved is off, take his team past 200 by smashing this full delivery over the covers for a boundary
full toss on middle, tries to ram it over midwicket, mistimes it over the bowler's head for a couple of runs
bowled full on middle, mistimes an attempted slog to midwicket for a single

inn2.comm: Australia off the mark straightaway, bowled on a good length outside off, takes a stride forward and pushes it past mid-off for a couple of runs, will be relieved, hasn't been doing well at the top of late
crashed through extra cover, sped off the bat,. a juicy half-volley on the off stump, gets to the pitch and smashes it through the off side for a boundary
banged in short on middle, a good comeback from Gul, bouncer, ducks under it comfortably
straying on the pads, tries to drive it through midwicket, is struck on the pads but that would have slid down
more runs, pitches it up outside off, Watson, in a positive mood, gets forward and drives it elegantly wide of mid-off for a boundary, another half-volley
hurls it short of a length outside off, chopped down to point
starts off with a wide down the leg side, some nerves surely
gets it on target this time, bowled on a good length outside off, gets a thick inside edge as he tries to defend it on the off side
just settling in is Asif, 130 kmph, good length outside off, holds its line, left alone to the keeper
another wide down the leg side, getting his direction wrong in his first over, bowling at this level after a long time, more than 18 months
nicely done, shaping away from the right hander, gets it to land on a driving length and moves away, Paine shoulders arms to that one
bowled at 128.3 kmph, short of a good length on the off, moves back and defends it on the off side
pushed it fuller on the off stump, moves back and drops it back to the bowler
aggression, picked it up beautifully and timed it even better, fullish on the off, moved across and clipped it into the stands behind deep midwicket, ominous signs for Pakistan first up
four more, short of a good length outside off, smart play from Watson who runs it down past a diving slip to the third-man boundary
beaten, short of a good length on the off and darts away to just escape the outside edge
edged and short, identical delivery to the previous one, much closer to the off stump, gets a thin edge and it lands short of a diving Akmal
back of a length on middle, bowled from wide of the crease, defended onto the pitch
banged in short on the off, tries to pull it hard over midwicket, doesn't time it well, more elevation than distance, has enough on it to roll over the ropes, four more
slightly short on the off, gets on the back foot and guides it down to point
bowled on a good length on middle, shuffles across and drives it down to mid-on
Asif unlucky, bowled full outside off, goes for a booming drive through cover, gets an inside edge wide of short fine down to the fine-leg boundary
good length on the off, defended with a lunge to cover
poor stuff from Asif, bowled full outside off, driven hard and handsome through extra cover, beats mid-off, and races to the fence
short and wide, cut away down to third man for a single
back of a length on the off at 129.5 kmph, punched straight to extra cover
bowled on a good length on the off, reaches forward and taps it to point
short of a good length on the off, dabs it down to point off the back foot
bowled full on the off, driven straight to mid-off, confidently done, no sign of nerves

tight line on the off stump, gets forward and pushes it to cover
shortish on the off, bowled at 86.2 kmph, waits for it to turn in and nudges it into the leg side for a single

good length on the off, gets forward and pushed to extra cover

dipping in towards middle, turned wide of midwicket

gets off the mark, pushed wide of cover for a single
